    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it just feels like a math problem to me lately. like if you look at the universe as a whole, there's no objective scale for value. if nothing has inherent meaning, then the sum of all existence is basically zero. so how can choosing to stay be any more \"meaningful\" than choosing to leave? logically, it's just two different ways to reach zero.",
